If you are thinking of taking the hike to the top of Half Dome its a strenuous hike of over 17  miles from the Valley Floor with an elevation of over 4,000 before you reach the the steep granite domes.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Park Geek® in Zion National Park with @zionnps, @zionforeverproject, and @theexplorepaige_. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Hike a river. Hike an unforgettable day. Hike Zion. 
•••••
Thanks to Paige  @theexplorepaige_ for the excellent adventure. 
•
Bucket List: Hike the Narrows ✔️ 

If you have time for only one hike while at Zion I HIGHLY recommend the Narrows! 🥾 
We rented our hiking stick, waterproof shoes and socks from Zion Outfitters before hopping on the shuttle to the trail head. When I say those three items make all the difference I am not exaggerating. We tried hiking the Narrows two years ago and thought “oh we should be fine with water shoes (the kind for pools) and we’ll just hold each others hands for support” boy oh boy we’re we wrong lol 😅 we were slipping ALL over the place and didn’t even make it a mile in before having to turn back 😭 
We were able to go 5 miles in and the views continued to blow me away the further in we got, I didn’t want to stop but we knew the further we go in we’d have to go the same distance back. We did a total of 10 miles and it was more than worth it 😉
☀️Mini Itinerary ☀️ 
7am: picked up our gear rental 
7:30am: Hopped on the shuttle 
8:00am: Started the walk to the Narrows Trailhead 
8:30am-5pm: hiked The Narrows 
5:30pm: hopped into the shuttle back to visitors center 
6pm: returned our gear 
6:30pm: Picked up stickers at the bookstore before heading back to our bnb

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by National Park Geek® on September 11, 2021 tagging @chrisriefphoto, and @flight93_nps. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Today we remember the 20th anniversary of the 9/11 attacks. The Flght 93 Memorial @flight93_nps tells of the stories of heroism and tragedy from that day. May we never forget. 🙏🇺🇸
•••••
Many thanks to NP Geek Ambassador Chris  @chrisriefphoto for sharing from @flight93_nps in PA. 
•
The Tower of Voices is conceived as a monumental, ninety-three feet tall musical instrument holding forty wind chimes, representing the forty passengers and crew members. The intent is to create a set of forty tones (voices) that can connote through consonance the serenity and nobility of the site while also through dissonance recalling the event that consecrated the site.⁣
-- @nationalparkservice⁣
⁣
📍 @flight93_nps #FindYourPark #Honor93 #WeRemember #20thObservance #NeverForget @nationalparkgeek #NationalParkGeek
